sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User
    participant F as Frontend
    participant G as API Gateway
    participant Svc as service-users
    participant Redis as Redis
    participant PG as PostgreSQL

    Note over U,F: User attempts to login

    F->>G: POST /api/auth/login<br/>{email, password}
    G->>Svc: Forward request
    Svc->>PG: Verify credentials
    PG-->>Svc: User data (hashed password)
    Svc->>Svc: bcrypt.compare()
    
    alt Credentials valid
        Svc->>Svc: Generate JWT tokens
        Svc->>Redis: Store refresh token
        Redis-->>Svc: OK
        Svc-->>G: {accessToken, refreshToken, user}
        G-->>F: Login successful
        F->>F: Store tokens in localStorage
    else Credentials invalid
        Svc-->>G: 401 Unauthorized
        G-->>F: Login failed
    end

    Note over U,F: Token refresh (before expiry)

    F->>G: POST /api/auth/refresh<br/>{refreshToken}
    G->>Svc: Forward request
    Svc->>Redis: Verify refresh token
    Redis-->>Svc: Token valid
    
    alt Token valid
        Svc->>Svc: Generate new access token
        Svc-->>G: {accessToken}
        G-->>F: Token refreshed
    else Token expired/invalid
        Svc-->>G: 401 Unauthorized
        G-->>F: Redirect to login
    end

    Note over U,F: Logout

    F->>G: POST /api/auth/logout
    G->>Svc: Forward request
    Svc->>Redis: Delete refresh token
    Redis-->>Svc: OK
    Svc-->>G: OK
    G-->>F: Logged out
    F->>F: Clear tokens